you might as well make it last
a few days, you know?

132
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:40,900
One night, you can have it with
rice. One night, baked potato...

133
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:43,460
It's rock and roll, me.

134
00:08:43,460 --> 00:08:45,420
Well, I'm not complaining.

135
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:48,380
By the time I knock off, the only
thing that's open is a dodgy kebab.

136
00:08:48,380 --> 00:08:51,260
That's undercover, isn't it?
Stupid hours.

137
00:08:51,260 --> 00:08:53,340
Well, Mark works in IT.

138
00:08:53,340 --> 00:08:56,780
He did a lot from home,
which was great for childcare.

139
00:08:56,780 --> 00:08:58,340
Just not so great for us.

140
00:08:58,340 --> 00:09:01,420
You still see the kid, though? Yeah.

141
00:09:03,020 --> 00:09:06,460
Sorry, I shouldn't poke my nose in.
No, it's fine.

142
00:09:06,460 --> 00:09:10,620
It was the right decision. You know,
give him security and stability.

143
00:09:10,620 --> 00:09:13,740
Just not such a great
decision for me, to be honest.

144
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:16,460
See, me and my missus,
we never got around to having kids.

145
00:09:16,460 --> 00:09:20,100
Was she a copper too? Forensics.
I don't see much of her now.

146
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:22,900
No? No, I was on the
piss most nights.

147
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:24,500
Couldn't pass a bookie's.

148
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:27,940
Final straw was - we'd put down
half on a fortnight in Majorca.

149
00:09:27,940 --> 00:09:29,260
Oh, don't tell me.

150
00:09:29,260 --> 00:09:32,100
Yeah, five-to-one. Dead cert.

151
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:34,860
I couldn't go home to face
the music, so...

152
00:09:34,860 --> 00:09:36,540
I took out a loan,

153
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:41,100
put a grand down on the last race of
the day, try and win it all back...

154
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:45,660
Barrel of laughs, me, yeah.

155
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:49,580
Can I have your bowl? Cheers.

156
00:10:04,260 --> 00:10:06,380
Hey, there's seconds here
if you fancy?

157
00:10:06,380 --> 00:10:08,580
Any more
and I won't get off this sofa.

158
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:26,260
Yeah? I've got something
for you, Sarge.

159
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:28,900
"On that photo found at Danny's."
Yeah, sure.

160
00:10:30,220 --> 00:10:32,380
It's from a boys' home
called Sands View.

161
00:10:32,380 --> 00:10:35,100
Danny Waldron's mum died when he
was 11, and he moved up north to

162
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:38,620
live with his dad and stepmum, but that
didn't work out and he got taken into care.

163
00:10:38,620 --> 00:10:42,260
Danny was a resident at Sands View
from the age of 13 until he was 17.

164
00:10:42,260 --> 00:10:43,860
I keep going through the file.

165
00:10:43,860 --> 00:10:47,740
There's no link between Danny Waldron and
Ronan Murphy while Danny was a police officer.

166
00:10:47,740 --> 00:10:49,700
The only link must
be this boys' home.

167
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:52,500
Unfortunately, I can't get
hold of any records for that period.

168
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:54,860
One council department
told me they were lost in a fire,

169
00:10:54,860 --> 00:10:57,300
another told me they went missing
during an office move.

170
00:10:57,300 --> 00:10:59,020
You think they've
been lost on purpose?

171
00:10:59,020 --> 00:11:01,780
Who knows? The lads were
chucked out at 17 and pretty much

172
00:11:01,780 --> 00:11:04,100
left to fend for themselves,
with no follow-up.

173
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:06,740
However, I've crosschecked
with individuals known

174
00:11:06,740 --> 00:11:09,380
to the criminal justice system
and I've got a name for you.

175
00:11:09,380 --> 00:11:10,500
Same age as Danny,

176
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:13,180
so chances are they were
there at the same time.

177
00:11:13,180 --> 00:11:15,060
Good work.

178
00:11:24,740 --> 00:11:26,540
Hey, Joe. Joe!

179
00:11:29,140 --> 00:11:30,820
Joseph Nash? Yeah?

180
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:34,340
Can I talk to you
somewhere quieter, please?

181
00:11:34,340 --> 00:11:35,540
Yeah.

182
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:48,500
I'd like to show you a photograph,
if that's all right.

183
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:52,220
It's a photocopy of an original
image believed to be

184
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:55,180
