a number of minor offences.

190
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:14,940
Look, I was just a kid, back then.

191
00:12:14,940 --> 00:12:18,380
I've put my life back together now.
The convictions are spent.

192
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:22,100
It was only that your record crosschecked
with an enquiry I'm involved with.

193
00:12:28,140 --> 00:12:30,100
An enquiry into Sands View?

194
00:12:30,100 --> 00:12:31,860
Connected to Sands View.

195
00:12:34,020 --> 00:12:36,020
Do you recognise this individual?

196
00:12:37,380 --> 00:12:39,460
Yes, Danny. Danny Waldron. Yeah.

197
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:42,380
Do you recognise this individual?

198
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:43,740
Yes.

199
00:12:45,460 --> 00:12:47,940
What do you remember
about that person?

200
00:12:47,940 --> 00:12:50,660
He took us for football on
a Tuesday afternoon.

201
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:53,540
He was one of the staff?
No, he just took us for footie.

202
00:12:53,540 --> 00:12:55,340
What else do you recall about him?

203
00:12:58,860 --> 00:13:00,820
You're being a big help, Joe.

204
00:13:02,380 --> 00:13:04,740
Is it OK if I ask you
about one more person?

205
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:08,420
This man, here.

206
00:13:08,420 --> 00:13:09,460
Him.

207
00:13:10,860 --> 00:13:12,740
Who is he?

208
00:13:14,140 --> 00:13:16,260
Mr Murphy. He was the caretaker.

209
00:13:16,260 --> 00:13:17,820
The other man.

210
00:13:17,820 --> 00:13:21,460
The football coach. Was his name
Murphy too? Might have been.

211
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:24,660
They was a pair.

212
00:13:24,660 --> 00:13:26,140
A pair?

213
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:32,180
The older one, the caretaker,
he had the keys.

214
00:13:34,740 --> 00:13:36,500
For the dormitories.

